We know that the number of drinks is $\maroonD{22}$, so we have:

$\begin{align}
[\maroonD{\text{number of drinks}}]\cdot [\greenD{\text{price per drink}}]&=\blueD{\text{total price}}\\\\
\maroonD{22}(\greenD{x-0.35})&=\blueD{18.70}
\end{align}$

This shows us that $\greenD{x-0.35}$ is the price Jenny paid per drink.

We know that the director spent $\green{93\dfrac{3}{4}}$ hours on other responsibilities, so we have:

$\begin{align}
[\maroonD{\text{hours of rehearsal}}] + [\greenD{\text{other hours}}]&=\blueD{\text{total hours preparing}} \\\\
[\maroonD{35x}] + \left[\greenD{93\dfrac{3}{4}}\right]&=\blueD{190}
\end{align}$

This shows us that $\maroonD{35x}$ is the number of hours the director spent attending rehearsals.

We know that the number of meters of string for the first yo-yo is $\maroonD{1\dfrac34}$ and the length of the string for the second yo-yo is $\goldE{1}$ meter, so we have:

$\begin{align}
[\maroonD{\text{length for yo-yo }1}] + [\goldE{\text{length for yo-yo }2}]+ [\greenD{\text{length for yo-yo }3}]&=\blueD{\text{total length}}\\\\
\maroonD{1\dfrac{3}{4}} + \goldE{1}+\greenD{y}&=\blueD{4\dfrac{1}{3}}
\end{align}$

This shows us that $\greenD{y}$ is the length, in meters, of the string for the third yo-yo.

We know that the administrative fee is $\greenD{3.50}$ dollars, so we have:

$\begin{align}
[\blueD{\text{total charge}}]&=[\maroonD{\text{charge based on kWh}}] +[\greenD{\text{administrative fee}}]\\\\
\blueD{63.25}&=\maroonD{800r} +\greenD{3.50}
\end{align}$

This shows us that $\maroonD{800r}$ is the part of the cost that depends on the number of kilowatt-hours.
